    <thetext>Tests and fix released via http://git.eclipse.org/c/jdt/eclipse.jdt.core.git/commit/?h=BETA_JAVA8&amp;id=abe6a4b8c7a37b999ce782468f77dcc11e925eae

Types allowed for casting to primitive:
- all reference types (incl. type variables) except
  - boxing types
  - arrays

Note, that the mention of arrays is lacking from the spec but javac as well as common sense tell us that no array can be cast-unbox converted into a primitive.</thetext>
